"{\"uid\": \"hngn.com-articles-262511-20240805-olympics-last-supper-drag-show-vatican-responds.htm\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Vatican has finally responded to thecontroversial drag performancethat portrayed Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"Last Supper\\\" painting during the open ceremony for the 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 85, \"end\": 102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.019936070772119e-19, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Sunday,the Vatican expressed\\\"sadness and regret\\\" at some parts of the July 26  performance, saying it revealed a lack of \\\"respect for others.\\\"\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Vatican said it \\\"cannot but join the voices raised in recent days to deplore the offense done to many Christians and believers of other religions,\\\" the statement added.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 436, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.931219014352321, \"rank\": 0.04637504312804963, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The featured scene appeared similar to the famous Last Supper painting of Jesus Christ by Leonardo da Vince and his apostles sharing a final meal, but with drag queens at the center of a banquet.\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"score\": 0.9999999999998863, \"rank\": 1.3982245920831501e-13, \"text\": \"Last Supper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\"}, {\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9971352979805019, \"rank\": 0.002872930578977528, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.423900302577729e-14, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The central figure was a woman dressed in a large silver headdress, resembling a halo as often seen in depictions of Jesus Christ.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9971352979805019, \"rank\": 0.002872930578977528, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At a prestigious event where the whole world comes together to share common values, there should be no allusions ridiculing the religious convictions of many people.\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The freedom of expression, which is clearly not called into question here, is limited by respect for others,\\\" the Vatican said.\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The event's creative director claimed the scene was not intended to reference Da Vinci's painting, but France's love of food and feasting.\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.266151656254614e-23, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8672727541995329, \"rank\": 0.14992957233738077, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also characterized the performance as a celebration of tolerance and freedom.\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"AnOlympics spokesperson, however, apologizedto those the performance offended and later admitted to the allusion.\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2025 HNGN, All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not reproduce without permission.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": []}]}"